question: Pick a set of figures from history for your own special dinner party where you get to talk to them.
answer:
Napoleon Bonaparte, Elizabeth I and Leonardo da Vinci.

I'll write from Napoleon's POV.
----------

"How do you take your guests?" asked Madeleine, who had moved in as my housekeeper when I took over from my grandfather Antoine.

"I like them young, full of life. And with their homework on history, I get to learn what doesn't interest me, like the 15th century"

"Don't believe I've seen Queen Elizabeth I on your guest list" Madeleine remarked.

"Are you sure? I'm pretty sure I invited her last March."

"She didn't show."

"She's got a dictator fetish, ask her about it. I'm sure she'll be delighted to talk about it."

Later that evening as my guests hung their coats in the cloakroom, I pulled Madeleine aside and had her hand me a note I found in Elizabeth's coat pocket.

"Take a look at this?" I murmured, sipping my damn good martini.

Madeleine read aloud, "'Send escort home before seducing. Time spent at dinner not wasted. EI'."

"Madeleine, I need you to keep an eye on the Queen this evening. She's prone to wandering. I don't have the energy to put her in bed again."

I made my way back into the main salon, where Marie Antoinette (perhaps too young and too dainty for me) was holding court over a bowl of grapes and pita bread and hummus.

"Bored with the hunt?" I asked.

"It's really quite fun when the hunt is on," she replied, pirouetting.

I thanked my grandfather for inviting her. She looked at me as if to say, 'you're welcome' but instead smiled wanly and curtsied.

Night fell. My guests ambled from room to room, ideologies and centuries clashing. The banter was lively; Elizabeth was winning over the youth but backed off as I got close. Marie Antoinette danced her way to my study, followed closely by my youngest royals - teenage boys with far too much time on their hands.

At midnight, as I sat in my chair looking up at an owl in the tree, Madeleine informed me Elizabeth was waiting in my bed, naked. My eyelids descended as I contemplated that piece of information.
